article.description: Murray St rolls, tops Jacksonville St 73-65
article.headline: Murray St rolls, tops Jacksonville St 73-65
article.linkText: Murray St rolls, tops Jacksonville St 73-65
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Jeffery Moss and Cameron Payne both scored 16 points as Murray State won its eighth straight, turning away Jacksonville State, 73-65 Saturday night. Brian Williams made the first of two free throws with 41 seconds left to cut the Racers' lead to four points, 69-65, but Jarvis Williams hit a pair of free throws and capped the scoring with a dunk to put the game away. Darion Rackley was fouled on a 3-point attempt and converted all three free throws, then added a layup to give Jacksonville State the lead, 44-41 with under 15 minutes to play, but Murray State answered with a 10-0 run to take control. Jarvis Williams scored 13 points and Dexter Fields added 10 as Murray State (12-8, 7-1 Ohio Valley) opened a three-game West Division lead. Jacksonville State (10-14, 4-5) got 18 points from Rackley, 15 from Avery Moore and 14 from Brian Williams.
